{"id":502078,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/William_Pfaff","text":"William Pfaff (December 1928 \u2013 April 30, 2015) was an American writer. He was an author and op-ed columnist for the \"International Herald Tribune\". He also worked on \"The New York Review of Books\".\nPfaff was born in Council Bluffs, Iowa. He was of German, English, and Irish ancestry. He studied at the University of Notre Dame. He was a Catholic and was married with two children.\nPfaff died from a heart attack caused by a fall on April 30, 2015 in Paris, France. He was 86.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Americans","surface_form":"American","offset":54},{"uri":"Writer","surface_form":"writer","offset":63},{"uri":"Author","surface_form":"author","offset":81},{"uri":"Op-ed","surface_form":"op-ed","offset":92},{"uri":"Columnist","surface_form":"columnist","offset":98},{"uri":"International_Herald_Tribune","surface_form":"International Herald Tribune","offset":117},{"uri":"The_New_York_Review_of_Books","surface_form":"The New York Review of Books","offset":167},{"uri":"Council_Bluffs%2C_Iowa","surface_form":"Council Bluffs","offset":216},{"uri":"Iowa","surface_form":"Iowa","offset":232},{"uri":"Germans","surface_form":"German","offset":248},{"uri":"English_people","surface_form":"English","offset":256},{"uri":"Irish_people","surface_form":"Irish","offset":269},{"uri":"Ancestry","surface_form":"ancestry","offset":275},{"uri":"University_of_Notre_Dame","surface_form":"University of Notre Dame","offset":303},{"uri":"Catholic","surface_form":"Catholic","offset":338},{"uri":"Heart_attack","surface_form":"heart attack","offset":400},{"uri":"Fall","surface_form":"fall","offset":425},{"uri":"Paris","surface_form":"Paris","offset":451},{"uri":"France","surface_form":"France","offset":458}]}